div.div: This is an example of Operator Overloading. Here the "+" sign is being overloaded to concatenate (or add) two strings together. The base function of the "+" operator is calculate the sum of two numbers but Java is internally overloading the "+" to concatenate when the arguments are comprised of strings. Custom overload operators are not allowed in Java. These are built-in functionalities.

div.div: This is an example of Function Overloading. Methods can have the same name with different parameters and return type (optional). This functionality is useful when an Object or Sub-Class needs to carry out an existing method but in a different way.
